      "content": "it's not really about taking a break though. i mean, when you look at a map and you realize you've seen every landmark, every street, every single thing worth seeing... there isn't really a \"next destination\" that matters. there is just the empty space where the map ends. it feels more like i've completed the tour and now i'm just waiting for the last train to take me out of the station. it just feels so much more peaceful to think about that final departure than to keep wandering aimlessly through cities i don't even care about anymore.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
